txt.en: 'Ah, I see you have finally arrived.'
As the Ancient Spirit dies, a door locks in the distance.
'Now it is time for this to end.'
As Gorothul dies, a large door opens loudly nearby.
'Who dares call me forth?'
Flames begin to fill Urchír's chamber.
This chest can only be used if you have defeated Gorothul without defeating the other two bosses.
'These corpses are becoming troublesome.'
'My lord Sauron, what should I do?'
'Yes, my lord.'
'Intruders!  Get them!'
'We give you our strength, Master!'
'You are too quick for your own good.  Run while you still can!'
Doors open in the distance as endless waves of Black Uruks stream forth
'Through his eyes, you are revealed, [placeholder].'
'Even while I am not here, my servants will crush your pitiful attempts to re-take Dol Guldur.'
'Let terror take you!'
'Gorothul!  Destroy the Free Peoples who dare to intrude upon this my fortress of old!'
'From this point forward, I will teach you the true meaning of terror!'
This chest can only be used if you have defeated Gorothul.
'We are through.  Burning will be your only remaining choice!'
'The storms are gathering quickly.'
Sauron[mn]
The air crackles as lightning begins to strike Sammath Gûl.
'My lord, aid me!'
This chest is useable once Urchír is killed.
'The storm's pace hastens. It is only a matter of time now.'
'This chest is useable once Alagossír is killed.'
'This has gone on for too long!  Spirits aid me!'
